      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNIVERSAL HARMONY (5) returned from a spell three weeks ago when he was beaten 5 lengths into fourth over 1050m at Rockhampton. Has never missed the placings at the second run back. Likely improver with strong prospects. DEALING'S DONE (2) was comfortably accounted for when sixth last time out over 1100m at this track, beaten 3.5 lengths. That followed a win here at the previous outing. The engagement of Warwick Satherley is a positive move and is a likely improver with strong prospects. OUTBACK BANDIT (7) finished 2.8 lengths back from the winner last start at Rockhampton on soft going and is down in weight this time. Sound record at this distance with three wins and five minor placings from 11 runs and is one of the leading contenders. UPSTART LEGEND (9) was in the placings when a length away from the winner last time at Mt Garnet. Winning rider Adam Sewell sticks and must be respected.",
